<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,726,931]" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,260,726,751]" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">Remarks</emphasis>
. The status of the 
<collectingRegion box="[496,561,726,751]" country="Cameroon" name="South" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">South</collectingRegion>
American 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Michaelsen" authorityYear="1907" box="[698,794,726,751]" class="Clitellata" family="Acanthodrilidae" genus="Eodrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opisthopora" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[698,794,726,751]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">Eodrilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species is quite controversial, as its 
<typeStatus box="[1243,1291,727,751]" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Michaelsen, 1907" authorityName="Michaelsen" authorityYear="1907" class="Clitellata" family="Acanthodrilidae" genus="Eodrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opisthopora" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="cornigravei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">Eo. cornigravei</emphasis>
Michaelsen, 1907
</taxonomicName>
toghether with the other Australian 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Michaelsen" authorityYear="1907" box="[903,999,762,787]" class="Clitellata" family="Acanthodrilidae" genus="Eodrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opisthopora" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[903,999,762,787]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">Eodrilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species was transferred to 
<taxonomicName authority="Spencer, 1900" authorityName="Spencer" authorityYear="1900" class="Clitellata" family="Acanthodrilidae" genus="Diplotrema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opisthopora" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1308,1436,762,787]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">Diplotrema</emphasis>
Spencer, 1900
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[324,593,798,823]" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" refId="ref13853" refString="Jamieson, B. G. M. &amp; Dyne, G. (1976) The Acanthodrile earthworm genus Microscolex (Diplotrema) (Megascolecidae: Oligochaeta) in the Northern Territory of Australia. Australian Journal of Zoology, 24, 445 - 476. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / ZO 9760445" type="journal article">Jamieson &amp; Dyne 1976</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[605,739,799,823]" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" refId="ref13651" refString="James, S. W. (1990) Diplotrema murchiei and D. papillata, new earthworms (Oligochaeta: Megascolecidae) from Mexico. Acta Zoologica Mexicana, 38, 18 - 27." type="journal article">James 1990</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[751,1022,798,823]" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" refId="ref14933" refString="Reynolds, J. W. &amp; Righi, G. (1994) On some earthworms from Belize, C. A. with the description of a new species (Oligochaeta: Acanthodrilidae, Glossoscolecidae and Octochaetidae). Megadrilogica, 5, 97 - 106." type="journal article">Reynolds &amp; Righi 1994</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[1033,1222,798,823]" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" refId="ref11930" refString="Blakemore, R. J. (1997) Two new genera and some new species of Australian earthworms (Acanthodrilidae, Megascolecidae: Oligochaeta). Journal of Natural History, 31, 1785 - 1848. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222939700770951" type="journal article">Blakemore 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation pageId="2" pageNumber="13" refId="ref13231" refString="Fragoso, C. &amp; Brown, G. G. (2007) Ecologia y taxonomia de las lombrices de tierra en Latinoamerica: El primer Encuentro Latino-Americano de Ecologia y Taxonomia de Oligoquetos (ELAETAO 1). In: Brown, G. G. &amp; Fragoso, C. (Eds.), Minhocas na America Latina: Biodiversidade e Ecologia. Embrapa, Londrina, pp. 33 - 75. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.2004.00146. x" type="book chapter">Fragoso &amp; Brown 2007</bibRefCitation>
). The 
<collectingRegion box="[282,348,834,859]" country="Cameroon" name="South" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">South</collectingRegion>
African 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Michaelsen" authorityYear="1907" box="[448,545,834,859]" class="Clitellata" family="Acanthodrilidae" genus="Eodrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opisthopora" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[448,545,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">Eodrilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species were removed and accomodated in 
<taxonomicName authority="Zicsi, 1998" authorityName="Zicsi" authorityYear="1998" box="[1040,1308,834,859]" class="Clitellata" family="Acanthodrilidae" genus="Eodriloides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opisthopora" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1040,1171,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">Eodriloides</emphasis>
Zicsi, 1998
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<collectingRegion box="[1371,1436,834,859]" country="Cameroon" name="South" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">South</collectingRegion>
American species are maintained here in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Michaelsen" authorityYear="1907" box="[620,716,870,895]" class="Clitellata" family="Acanthodrilidae" genus="Eodrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opisthopora" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[620,716,870,895]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">Eodrilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, until a statisfactory solution is found, following Reynolds and Righi (1997) and 
<bibRefCitation box="[349,655,906,931]" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" refId="ref13231" refString="Fragoso, C. &amp; Brown, G. G. (2007) Ecologia y taxonomia de las lombrices de tierra en Latinoamerica: El primer Encuentro Latino-Americano de Ecologia y Taxonomia de Oligoquetos (ELAETAO 1). In: Brown, G. G. &amp; Fragoso, C. (Eds.), Minhocas na America Latina: Biodiversidade e Ecologia. Embrapa, Londrina, pp. 33 - 75. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.2004.00146. x" type="book chapter">Fragoso and Brown (2007)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
